detail.title: v1.1 Upgrade
detail.description:
### **Title:**
Cudos Testnet v1.1 Upgrade

**Type:**
Software Upgrade Proposal

**Description:**

Summary: Upgrade the Cudos Public Testnet to v1.1

The release notes for the changes to the network can be found here:

[https://github.com/CudoVentures/cudos-node/releases/tag/v1.1.0](https://github.com/CudoVentures/cudos-node/releases/tag/v1.1.0)

The items in the release are:

General:



* Implement In-Store upgrades
* Implement cosmos-sdk fix to validator edit bug
* Add "--dry-run" flag fix to Cosmos SDK

NFT Module:



* Fix abnormal behaviour from NFT Module REST API
* Optimise NFT denom creation
* New features

NFT related:



* NFT marketplace module
* NFT royalties
* TransferDenom functionality refactoring
* Tests for the NFT Marketplace & Address Book Modules
* Fix marketplace module ID's generation
* Add verification to marketplace collections
* Additional messages for NFT marketplace module

Gravity Module:



* Add `getPendingSendToEthTransactions` REST endpoint
* Functionality for Canceling Gravity Bridge Transaction
* Add tests for cancelSendToEth message

Addressbook:



* Address book module

Authz module:



* Enable authz module
* Add authz non determinism module fix

Group module:



* Cosmos Group module research:
* Implementation of "Failed" transaction type 


By voting YES on this proposal, you agree that the Cudos v1.1 upgrade should proceed, and the changes in the release notes above should be implemented.

By voting NO on this proposal, you disagree that the Cudos v1.1 upgrade should happen, and the changes in the release notes above should be implemented.

By voting NO WITH VETO, you disagree with the Cudos v1.1 upgrade taking place, and additionally wish to see depositors penalized. 

By voting ABSTAIN, you decline to give an opinion on the upgrade. 

Treasury: This proposal does not affect the treasury

Testing: This proposal has been implemented and tested on a private development network

detail.title: Cudos block time estimation to 6.25 seconds
detail.description:
This proposal aims to recalibrate the parameter, "IncrementModifier", that corresponds to the expected number of blocks produced in a day. This parameter affects the amount of staking rewards minted at each block, and therefore it should be as close to the reality as possible in order to ensure a full and sustainable reward distribution to our community, following the Cudos token release curve.

Through a proposal on 25 August, 2022, (proposal #7) we set this parameter to 12345, which corresponds to an average block time of 7 seconds. Our aim was to set it to a value so that rewards would be released faster than the regular release schedule in order to compensate for the initial period during which the rewards were not being released in full. We promised in that proposal to set the parameter back to its correct value once the compensation period has been completed, and that time has come. Consequently, we are submitting this proposal to set this parameter to 13824, which corresponds to an average block time of 6.25 seconds as has been observed since the last proposal. In the meantime, we will continue to monitor block times, and take action as necessary.

detail.title: Cudos block time estimation to 7 seconds
detail.description: This proposal aims to update the block time estimation used to distribute the new tokens that are minted, according to the Cudos token release curve. This parameter should be as close to the average block time as possible, and currently it's lower, so we are setting it higher in this proposal to compensate for this initial period and address the current discrepancy with the APR shown in the explorer. Three months after this proposal was sent, another proposal will be created to set it to the average block time, allowing the network to continue its intended token release schedule.
